<L>Like rivala to his choice, what human brea&s;t</L>
<L N="230">E'er doubts before the tran&s;ient and minute</L>
<L>To prize the va&s;t, the &s;table, the &s;ublime?</L>
<L>Who that from heights aerial &s;ends his eye</L>
<L>Around a wild horizon, and &s;urveys</L>
<L><PB N="125" REF="125">
Indus or Ganges rolling his broad wave</L>
