<L N="290"><PB N="127" REF="127">
Too lowly, I account in which to clothe</L>
<L>Thy form divine! for thee the mind alone</L>
<L>Beholds, nor half thy brightne&s;s can reveal</L>
<L>Thro' tho&s;e dim organs who&s;e corporeal touch</L>
<L>O'er&s;hadoweth thy pure e&s;&s;ence. Yet my Mu&s;e!</L>
<L N="295">If Fortune call thee to the ta&s;k, wait thou</L>
