<L N="350">Cover'd with fleeces to the lowing vale</L>
<L>Reply, where tidings of content and peace</L>
<L>Each echo brings. Lo how the we&s;tern fun</L>
<L>O'er fields and floods, o'er ev'ry living &s;oul,</L>
<L>Diffu&s;eth glad repo&s;e! There while I &s;peak</L>
<L N="355">Of Beauty's honours thou, Meli&s;&s;a! thou</L>
<L>Shalt hearken, not uncon&s;cious, while I tell</L>
<L>How fir&s;t from heav'n &s;he came, how after all</L>
